### 71. THE DISEASE OF KNOWLEDGE.

<span id="img_tao71"></span>

|                    |
|--------------------|
| ![](img/tao71.jpg) |

1\. To know the unknowable, that is elevating. Not to know the knowable,
that is sickness.

2\. Only by becoming sick of sickness can we be without sickness.

3\. The holy man is not sick. Because he is sick of sickness, therefore
he is not sick.

